# Keep AGENTS.md Updated

After making logical changes to the project (adding, removing, or renaming files/directories; changing architecture, conventions, or component behavior), check whether `AGENTS.md` still accurately describes the project. If any documented section is now outdated, update it to reflect the new state.

Examples of changes that should trigger a review:
- Adding or removing a script, stylesheet, or HTML page
- Changing the theming approach or CSS custom-property contract
- Altering image-gallery behavior or naming conventions
- Modifying the top-action-button pattern or layout strategy
